{
  "name": "Chain Pull",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Icons/Bukijutsu.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You throw your weapon wrapping it around a target and pulling towards yourself. The target must succeed a Strength saving throw. On a failed save they are moved 10 feet closer to you in a straight line, cannot make handsigns until the beginning of their next turn, and also become restrained by you. At the end of the target creatures' turns, they can make a Strength saving throw to escape the restrain.</p><p>If this jutsu is cast as a Chain 2, you can target an additional creature in range. If this jutsu is cast as a Chain 3, target creatures have disadvantage on the initial saving throw.</p>",
